cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on WiFi multicast for multimedia delivery, which involves networking (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The paper also presents a new algorithm for rate adaptation, which involves system design (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the experimental evaluation is conducted on a testbed, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC).
